---
import { Code } from "astro:components";
import Callout from "../components/Callout.astro";
import ContentLayout from "../layouts/ContentLayout.astro";
import { sitePath } from "../utils/sitePath";

const releaseLatest = "https://github.com/ajself/PersonaKit/releases/latest";

const verifyCommands = `# From the folder you downloaded into
shasum -a 256 -c PersonaKit.pkg.sha256`;

const sourceCommands = `git clone https://github.com/ajself/PersonaKit.git
cd PersonaKit
make build
make cli-install INSTALL_BIN_DIR="$HOME/.local/bin"`;

const verifyCli = "personakit --help";
---

<ContentLayout
  title="Install PersonaKit"
  eyebrow="Get PersonaKit"
  description="Two ways to get PersonaKit on your Mac: the signed installer for the app and CLI together, or build the CLI from source."
>
  <p>The walkthroughs on this site run the <code>personakit</code> CLI. Pick one of the paths below to get it on your <code>PATH</code>, then head to <a href={sitePath("start-here/")}>Start Here</a> to run your first contract.</p>

  <section class="paths" aria-label="The two install paths at a glance">
    <article class="path">
      <p class="path-kicker">Recommended</p>
      <h3>Download the installer</h3>
      <p>One signed, notarized <code>.pkg</code> that installs PersonaKit Studio <em>and</em> the <code>personakit</code> CLI.</p>
      <p class="path-meta">macOS 26.2 or later</p>
    </article>
    <article class="path">
      <p class="path-kicker">CLI only</p>
      <h3>Build from source</h3>
      <p>Compile and install just the <code>personakit</code> CLI. No app, works in any bin directory you choose.</p>
      <p class="path-meta">macOS 26+ with the Swift 6.2 toolchain</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <h2 id="installer">1. Download The Installer</h2>
  <p>This is the simplest path and the one most people want. The installer is signed with a Developer ID and notarized by Apple, so Gatekeeper opens it without a detour.</p>

  <p class="action-row">
    <a class="button-link download-cta" href={releaseLatest}>Download the latest release</a>
    <span class="cta-note">Grab <code>PersonaKit.pkg</code> from the release assets.</span>
  </p>

  <p>Open the downloaded <code>PersonaKit.pkg</code> and follow the installer. It places:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>PersonaKit Studio</strong> in <code>/Applications</code> &mdash; the visual contract-inspection app.</li>
    <li><strong>The <code>personakit</code> CLI</strong> in <code>/usr/local/bin</code>, which is already on the default macOS <code>PATH</code>.</li>
  </ul>

  <Callout>
    <p>Installing the <code>.pkg</code> gives you both surfaces at once. You do not need to build anything to use the CLI &mdash; open a new terminal after installing and <code>personakit</code> is ready.</p>
  </Callout>

  <h3>Verify it works</h3>
  <Code code={verifyCli} lang="bash" theme="github-dark" />
  <p>If the command prints the help text, the CLI is installed and on your <code>PATH</code>. You are ready for <a href={sitePath("start-here/")}>Start Here</a>.</p>

  <h3>Check the download (optional)</h3>
  <p>Each release ships a <code>PersonaKit.pkg.sha256</code> checksum next to the installer. Download both into the same folder, then confirm the file matches:</p>
  <Code code={verifyCommands} lang="bash" theme="github-dark" />
  <p>An <code>OK</code> line means the file is intact and untampered.</p>

  <h2 id="source">2. Build The CLI From Source</h2>
  <p>Choose this if you only want the CLI, want to install it somewhere other than <code>/usr/local/bin</code>, or are working on PersonaKit itself. It needs <strong>macOS 26 or later</strong> with the <strong>Swift 6.2 toolchain</strong> (Xcode 26).</p>

  <Code code={sourceCommands} lang="bash" theme="github-dark" />

  <p>The <code>Makefile</code> is the repo command surface; run <code>make help</code> to see every target. <code>make cli-install</code> installs to <code>INSTALL_BIN_DIR</code> &mdash; point it wherever you keep local binaries.</p>

  <Callout tone="warn">
    <p>Make sure <code>INSTALL_BIN_DIR</code> is on your <code>PATH</code>. <code>make cli-install</code> warns if the just-installed binary is not the one your shell resolves &mdash; a common sign that an earlier copy is shadowing it.</p>
  </Callout>

  <p>Confirm the install the same way:</p>
  <Code code={verifyCli} lang="bash" theme="github-dark" />

  <h2>Which Should I Use?</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>You want&hellip;</th>
        <th>Use</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>The app and CLI, the quick way</td>
        <td>The installer</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Just the CLI, in a custom location</td>
        <td>Build from source</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>To work on PersonaKit itself</td>
        <td>Build from source</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>To stay on a pinned version</td>
        <td>The installer for a specific <a href={releaseLatest}>release</a></td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Next Step</h2>
  <p>With the CLI installed, run a real contract end to end. The walkthrough follows a bundled example that lives in the repo, so to run it exactly you'll want a <a href="https://github.com/ajself/PersonaKit">clone</a> too &mdash; or scaffold your own root with <code>personakit init &lt;dir&gt;</code> and follow along against that.</p>
  <p class="action-row">
    <a class="button-link primary-next" href={sitePath("start-here/")}>Continue to Start Here</a>
  </p>
</ContentLayout>

<style>
  .paths {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 16px;
    margin: 24px 0 8px;
  }

  .path {
    min-width: 0;
    padding: 18px;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: var(--paper);
  }

  .path h3 {
    margin: 8px 0;
  }

  .path p {
    max-width: none;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .path-kicker {
    color: var(--blue);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 750;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }

  .path-meta {
    margin-top: 10px !important;
    font-size: 14px;
  }

  .action-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 12px;
    margin: 20px 0;
  }

  .download-cta {
    border-color: #8db3c9;
    background: #eef6fa;
    color: var(--blue);
    font-weight: 750;
  }

  .cta-note {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 15px;
  }

  .primary-next {
    border-color: #8db3c9;
    background: #eef6fa;
    color: var(--blue);
    font-weight: 750;
  }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .paths {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
